overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, seeking to validate its adherence to the provided specification
  and SOW. The assistant conducted a detailed analysis, identifying several
  critical gaps in the existing implementation. Subsequently, the assistant
  systematically addressed these deficiencies. Key enhancements included
  integrating a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness, complete with safety warnings
  for high scores, and implementing robust detection and reporting mechanisms
  for COMISA and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome. The reports were further enriched
  with a new "Resources & Next Steps" section, providing valuable external
  links. Additionally, the system now incorporates weighted scoring for
  Excessive Daytime Sleepiness and offers a significantly expanded CSV export
  that captures all questionnaire data. The implementation process involved
  careful modifications to types, validations, UI components, and report
  generation logic, ensuring all identified issues were resolved in line with
  the user's requirements.
